    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-11-12T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-11-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="1070"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1070">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.5151 Manchuria/17: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-11-12T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >November 12, 1937—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 12—3:18 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>744. Your 361, November 10, 5 p.m.<note n="55" xml:id="d1070fn55">Not printed; it
                        requested further information (893.5151 Manchuria/15).</note> Following from
                    Mukden.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“No. 7, November 11, noon. With reference to the Department’s telegram No.
                        333 to the Embassy at Peiping,<note n="56" xml:id="d1070fn56">October 19, 3
                            p.m., <ref target="#pg_930">p. 930</ref>.</note> I again called on
                        Director of the Foreign Office who assured me that he is taking steps to
                        remedy discriminatory treatment of revised exchange control law.”</p>
                </quote>
                <pb facs="0943" n="936" xml:id="pg_936"/>
                <p>Mukden has been instructed to keep Embassy fully informed of all
                    developments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
